# Content Pipeline Rules

Design content systems so they can later be managed through an internal admin dashboard.

Future dashboard modules:
- hero editor
- skill editor
- enemy editor
- boss editor
- equipment editor
- campaign editor
- daily challenge scheduler
- shop/event manager
- balance tuning dashboard
- player support tools

When creating content models:
- use stable IDs
- use schema versions
- separate display data from logic data
- keep validation centralized
- make preview/test data easy to generate
- keep configs human-readable

Do not require app releases for simple balance/content changes when Firebase/Remote Config can safely support it.

Never expose admin-only write paths to normal clients.
